suppressMessages(library(Seurat))

# This DEA was performed using scStudio: https://compbio.imm.medicina.ulisboa.pt/app/scStudio 
# scStudio employs the FindMarkers function available from the Seurat package
# Default parameters were used except for: test.use = "MAST" and logfc.threshold = -Inf 
dea <- readRDS("/mnt/nmorais-nfs/marta/shiny/scstudio/tokens/karine/dea.rds")
markers_c3 <- dea$r0.4_3vsOthers_MAST
markers_c3$neutral_rank <- abs(markers_c3$`Log2FC (mean)`)
markers_c3 <- markers_c3[order(markers_c3$neutral_rank, decreasing = TRUE),]
markers_c3
markers_c6 <- dea$rs0.4_6vsOthers_MAST
markers_c6$neutral_rank <- abs(markers_c6$`Log2FC (mean)`)
markers_c6 <- markers_c6[order(markers_c6$neutral_rank, decreasing = TRUE),]
markers_c6
rank_c3 <- as.data.frame(cbind(markers_c3$Gene, markers_c3$neutral_rank))

colnames(rank_c3) <- c("genes", "log2FC")
  
nrank_c3 <- as.numeric(as.character(rank_c3[,2]))

names(nrank_c3) <- rank_c3$genes
  
get_categories <-  msigdbr_collections()
  
hallmarks <-  msigdbr(species = "Mus musculus", category = "H")

hallmarks <- hallmarks %>% split(x = .$gene_symbol, f = .$gs_name)
  
gsea_result_c3 <- fgsea(pathways = hallmarks, eps = 0, stats = nrank_c3)
## Warning in preparePathwaysAndStats(pathways, stats, minSize, maxSize, gseaParam, : There are ties in the preranked stats (86.96% of the list).
## The order of those tied genes will be arbitrary, which may produce unexpected results.
results_tidy_c3 <- gsea_result_c3 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES))
  
results_tidy_c3
rank_c6 <- as.data.frame(cbind(markers_c6$Gene, markers_c6$neutral_rank))

colnames(rank_c6) <- c("genes", "log2FC")
  
nrank_c6 <- as.numeric(as.character(rank_c6[,2]))

names(nrank_c6) <- rank_c6$genes
  
get_categories <-  msigdbr_collections()
  
hallmarks <-  msigdbr(species = "Mus musculus", category = "H")

hallmarks <- hallmarks %>% split(x = .$gene_symbol, f = .$gs_name)
  
gsea_result_c6 <- fgsea(pathways = hallmarks, eps = 0, stats = nrank_c6)
## Warning in preparePathwaysAndStats(pathways, stats, minSize, maxSize, gseaParam, : There are ties in the preranked stats (82.35% of the list).
## The order of those tied genes will be arbitrary, which may produce unexpected results.
results_tidy_c6 <- gsea_result_c6 %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(NES))
  
results_tidy_c6
plotEnrichment(hallmarks[["HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE"]],
                      nrank_c3 ) + labs(title = "C3 - HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE")

plotEnrichment(hallmarks[["HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE"]],
                      nrank_c6 ) + labs(title = "C6 - HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE")

leading_edge_c3 <- results_tidy_c3[results_tidy_c3$pathway == "HALLMARK_INFLAMMATORY_RESPONSE",]$leadingEdge[[1]]

unique_genes <- unique(c(leading_edge_c3, leading_edge_c6))
rownames(markers_c3) <- markers_c3$Gene
rownames(markers_c6) <- markers_c6$Gene
df <- data.frame(Genes = unique_genes, 
                 Rank_c3 = markers_c3[unique_genes,]$`Log2FC (mean)`,
                 Rank_c6 = markers_c6[unique_genes,]$`Log2FC (mean)`)
df
gene_label <- rep("Common", 118)
gene_label[df$Genes %in% leading_edge_c3 & !(df$Genes %in% leading_edge_c6)] <- "Cluster 3"
gene_label[df$Genes %in% leading_edge_c6 & !(df$Genes %in% leading_edge_c3)] <- "Cluster 6"
table(gene_label)
## gene_label
## Cluster 3 Cluster 6    Common 
##        23        32        63
df$gene_label <- gene_label
genes <- c("B2m", "Tap1", "Psme2", "Psmb9", "Psme1", "Psmb8", "Psma3", "Psmb2", "H2-Q7")
label <- df$Genes

label[!(label %in% genes)] <- ""
anti_label <- df$Genes
anti_label[anti_label %in% genes] <- ""

ggplot(df) +
  geom_point( aes(x=Rank_c3, y=Rank_c6, col = gene_label)) +
  
  geom_label_repel(aes(x=Rank_c3, y=Rank_c6, label = anti_label), size = 13, max.overlaps = 5) +
  
  geom_label_repel(aes(x=Rank_c3, y=Rank_c6, label = label), size = 13,
                   force = 10, fontface = 'bold',) +  
  
  scale_color_manual(values=c("red","orange", "grey45"), name = "Leading edge genes")  + 
  ggtitle("Hallmark: Inflammatory response") +
        xlab("C3 rank") + 
        ylab("C6 rank") +
        theme( text = element_text(size=20)) +
  
  geom_hline(yintercept=0, linetype="dashed", 
                color = "blue", size=0.3) +
  geom_vline(xintercept=0, linetype="dashed", 
                color = "blue", size=0.3) +
  
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(-1, 2.5), xlim = c(-1,5), expand = FALSE)
